upter, just like the ones in Hate, and also drops the Tainted BP for the epic. Once Lured away from his post he was killed and his armor twisted to serve the will of Innoruk. He was then condemed by the clerics and paladins of Erudin to wander the plane of fear as an undead skelleton. When you talk to him in fear, he askes you if you will release his soul. The only way to release his soul is to grant him atonement. He lost that when he failed at his guard post. To grant him atonement you speak with a cleric in Erudin, Reknlon Gnallen,  who will not even say the name of Irak. He tells you to recover all of Irak's old armor wich was stolen, purify it, and bring it back to him. Then and only then will he grant you atonement. Irak gives you clues as to who has his armor. Once you get back his old armor and purify it, the cleric in Erudin gives you a mark of atonement. He then tells you that this mark alone is not enough to undo Irak's curruption. A symbol of sacrafice and nobility is also needed. This symbol is the Fiery Avenger. ( A whole other story / quest) You give the fiery avenger and the mark of atonement to Irak Altil in fear and that releases his soul. You in effect, grant him atonement. In return he gives you the epic. Whats funny is that when you release his soul he says he wil go now to sacrafice himself upon the spear of  pain. That threw me off hehe.<br><br>So in reality, the enitre story is really 3 stories. The soulfire, the Fiery Avenger, and the Fiery Defender. The 3 have nothing to do with eachother story wise, but they all tie into eachother when you are doing the epic. <p><img src="http://members.aol.com/cragzak/images/apostyl.jpg"> <Br> <b>Apostyl Stellein</b><Br><Blood and Loyalty</b><Br><b>Tarew Marr</b><Br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172826">Inspect</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujolit